com.k2.JavaFactory

Class JavaFactoryError

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Error
        • com.k2.JavaFactory.JavaFactoryError
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class JavaFactoryError
extends java.lang.Error
    MetaModelErrors are unchecked errors thrown by the MetaModel in response to conditions from which it is not expected that an application using the meta model would be able to recover. This is most typically the case during configuration of the meta model where unexpected conditions are generally fatal.
    Author:
    Simon Emmott
